$ Azure HDInsight

*Provision cloud Hadoop, Spark, R Server, HBase and Storm clusters*

*HDInsight* is Microsoft's implementation of → development/Apache/Spark.
-
Spark clusters in HDInsight are compatible with → Microsoft/Azure/products/Blob-Storage and → Microsoft/Azure/products/Data-Lake-Storage, so HDInsight Spark clusters
can process → development/Data[Data] stored in → Microsoft/Azure.

sa:

  *Resource Providers* for Azure HDInsight include
    • Microsoft.HDInsight
  See also → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/az/ResourceProvider/get[`get-azResourceProvider`]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel menu → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Data/Get-and-Transform-Data/Get-Data[Data -> Get & Transform Data -> Get Data] -> From → Microsoft/Azure -> From Azure HDInsight (HDFS)
